10. CONCLUSION AND PATH FORWARD

10.1 Technical Feasibility Assessment

The analysis presented in this volume demonstrates that Project Slingstone is fundamentally feasible with technology that either exists today or represents straightforward extensions of current capabilities. No physics breakthroughs are required; rather, the challenge lies in systems integration at an unprecedented scale in a novel environment.

10.2 Immediate Next Steps

1. Laboratory Prototype: Construct a 10-meter test track demonstrating 100g acceleration with 1 kg payloads.
2. Materials Testing: Characterize all critical materials (REBCO, composites, regolith simulants) under lunar thermal vacuum conditions.
3. Control Algorithms: Develop and validate the real-time control system for multi-segment excitation.
4. International Partnerships: Establish technical working groups for standardized interfaces.

10.3 Technology Readiness Level (TRL) Assessment

Subsystem Current TRL Target TRL (5 years) Critical Gaps
HTS magnets 6 9 Radiation effects, lunar manufacturing
Pulsed power 5 8 Cryogenic switching at MA scale
Lunar construction 4 7 Autonomous precision assembly
